HEADWORD: Heterophemy
<hw>Het`er*oph"e*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hetero-</ets> + Gr. <?/ voice, speech, fr. <?/ to
speak.]</ety> <def>The unconscious saying, in speech or in writing, of
that which one does not intend to say; -- frequently the very reverse of
the thought which is present to consciousness.</def><-- Freudian slip
--> <rj><au>R. G. White.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

